ConceptSnap – Learn by Explaining Platform

1️.  System Architecture (High-Level)
Client:
•	Web browser (HTML/CSS/JavaScript)
•	Single-page prototype with three screens: Select Concept → Explain → Learn
Backend (Optional/Future):
•	Node.js + Express
•	MariaDB database
Database:
•	Concepts table
•	Explanations table
•	Feedback table
•	User progress tracking table
Infrastructure / Deployment:
•	Static Deployment: Netlify / Vercel / GitHub Pages (current prototype)
•	Optional Dynamic Deployment:
o	AWS EC2 / Render / Railway for Node.js API
o	Docker container for backend
o	Nginx as reverse proxy





Diagram (textual representation):
Browser (Single HTML/JS/CSS)  
        │
        ▼
Static Server (Netlify / Vercel)  
        │
        ▼
(Optional) Backend API (Node.js + Express)  
        │
        ▼
MariaDB Database

2️. API Specification (Sample / Future)
Endpoint	Method	Description
/api/concepts	GET	Retrieve a list of available concepts
/api/explanations	POST	Submit a student explanation
/api/feedback/{explanationId}	GET	Retrieve feedback for a submitted explanation
/api/progress/{userId}	GET	Track student’s progress for each concept
Example: POST /api/explanations
Request Body:
{
  "userId": 1,
  "conceptId": 2,
  "content": "Photosynthesis is how plants convert sunlight into energy."
}
Response:
{
  "success": true,
  "explanationId": 101
}

3️. Deployed Prototype
Prototype Details:
•	Fully functional single-page web application (index.html)
•	Handles:
o	Concept selection
o	Writing an explanation
o	Viewing expert feedback with star rating and circular progress
Deployment:
•	Static deployment on Netlify / GitHub Pages
•	Public URL: (you will provide the actual link once deployed)
Functionality Demonstrated:
•	Select a concept
•	Submit explanation
•	Review feedback (ideal explanation, star rating, areas of improvement)

